      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: Alright kids, time to get up, um, you know, school's not gonna wait for us, so basically, let's get moving.Speaker 2: Okay so, sweetie, remember when we talked about getting dressed quickly, how about you guys get started on that.Speaker 3: But why do I have to wear a uniform, actually, I know that it's the rule, but can I wear my favorite shirt instead.Speaker 1: Um, no, you know, the thing is, uniforms are, uh, required, so just put it on, okay.Speaker 4: Mommy look, I made a snowflake, can I show it to daddy.Speaker 2: That's nice sweetie, but first, let's get you dressed, and then you can show it to daddy.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to show daddy something, look look.Speaker 1: Okay, buddy, what do you want to show me, uh, so basically, let me see.Speaker 3: I know that we have to leave early today, but can I finish my book, please.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, but just for a few minutes, we don't want to be late, so basically, let's hurry up.Speaker 4: I want pancakes, mommy, please please, can I have pancakes.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, we can make some pancakes, but just a few, because we need to get going soon.Speaker 1: Um, so, you know, I was thinking, maybe we</data>
