      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">just a few, because we need to get going soon.Speaker 1: Um, so, you know, I was thinking, maybe we can, uh, make some scrambled eggs too, so basically, let's do that.Speaker 5: No, no, I don't want eggs, I want cereal, why do we have to have eggs.Speaker 3: Actually, eggs are good for you, because they have protein, and stuff.Speaker 2: That's right, sweetie, eggs are a good choice, but you can have cereal if you want, how about that.Speaker 4: That's not fair, I want cereal too, mommy look, I'm making a face.Speaker 1: Okay, okay, so, you know, let's just, uh, calm down, and have a good breakfast, okay.Speaker 5: Look look, I made a mess, oh no, sorry daddy.Speaker 2: It's okay, sweetie, accidents happen, let's just clean it up, and move on.Speaker 3: Can I help with the cleaning, because I know that we need to, you know, work together.Speaker 1: Um, yeah, that's a great idea, so basically, let's all pitch in, and get it done.Speaker 4: I want to help too, mommy, please please, can I use the sponge.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, but be careful, because we don't want any more messes, so basically, just use it gently.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to use the sponge, why can't</data>
