      <data key="d20">so basically, just use it gently.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to use the sponge, why can't I.Speaker 1: Okay, buddy, you can help, but just, uh, hold the sponge, and let your sister do the cleaning, okay.Speaker 3: Actually, I think we should, you know, make a schedule, so we can, uh, get everything done on time.Speaker 2: That's a great idea, sweetie, let's make a schedule, and stick to it, so basically, let's do that.Speaker 4: Mommy look, I'm finished cleaning, can I have a pancake now.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, you can have a pancake, but just one, because we need to, you know, get going soon.Speaker 1: Um, so, you know, I was thinking, maybe we can, uh, listen to some music, on the way to school, so basically, let's do that.Speaker 5: Yeah, yeah, I want to listen to music, look look, I'm dancing.Speaker 3: Actually, I think we should, you know, study for our tests, instead of listening to music, because we need to, uh, focus.Speaker 2: That's a good idea, sweetie, but we can, uh, listen to music, and still study, so basically, let's do both.Speaker 4: I don't want to study, I want to play, mommy, please please.Speaker 1: Okay, okay, so, you know, let's just, uh, calm</data>
