      <data key="d17">[{"Time": "2025-01-03 07:46:00", "Location": "Home, dining area", "Audio": "Speaker 1: Okay, so basically, I'm trying to get these lunches packed, um, you know, before you guys head out to school, right?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget to put the carrot sticks in, and, okay so, how about some hummus for dipping?Speaker 3: But why do I always have to have carrot sticks, actually, I know that they're good for me, but can I have a cookie instead?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a picture for my lunchbox, can you please put it in?Speaker 1: Uh, sure thing, kiddo, so, let me just, uh, finish making this sandwich, the thing is, we're running a bit behind schedule.Speaker 2: Remember when we used to make those bento boxes for school, how about we try that again sometime?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a picture in my lunchbox, why not me?Speaker 3: Because, actually, you didn't make one, so, maybe next time, you can draw something and we'll put it in your lunchbox.Speaker 1: So, uh, what's the plan for after school today, do we have any, um, activities or anything?Speaker 2: Okay, so, let me check the schedule, sweetie, it looks like you have soccer practice, and, oh, I need to pick up some more granola bars.Speaker 4: I want granola bars, mommy, please please can I have one now?Speaker 5: No, why, I don't want granola bars, I want goldfish crackers, look look, I have a goldfish cracker in my hand.Speaker 2: Sweetie, not now, okay, we'll have snacks after school, and, um, let's get your backpacks ready.Speaker 1: The thing is, I have a meeting at work, and, uh, I need to, you know, get going soon, so basically, let's hurry up.Speaker 3: But why do you have to go to work, actually, can't you just stay home with us?Speaker 2: Because, sweetie, daddy has to work to, you know, provide for our family, and, okay so, let's get moving.Speaker 4: Mommy, I don't want to go to school, I want to stay home and play with my toys, that's not fair.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I don't want to go to school, I want to play with blocks, look look, I'm building a castle.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's, you know, get our coats and, um, head out the door, the thing is, we don't want to be late.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's get going, sweetie, and, oh, don't forget your lunchboxes, and, um, have a great day at school.Speaker 3: Actually, I'm going to go get my backpack, can I, uh, get a drink of water before we leave?Speaker 4: I want water, mommy, please please can I have a sip of water?Speaker 5: No, why, I don't want water, I want juice, look look, I have a juice box in my hand.Speaker 2: Sweetie, not now, okay, we'll have water at school, and, um, let's get going.Speaker 1: So, basically, let's, you know, get out the door, and, uh, have a great day, everyone, the thing is, I'll see you all after school.Speaker 3: But why do we have to leave so early, actually, I know that we don't want to be late, but can't we just, uh, leave a few minutes later?Speaker 2: Because, sweetie, we need to, you know, get to school on time, and, okay so, let's get moving.Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I'm wearing my favorite dress, can you please take a picture of me?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a picture, look look, I'm making a funny face.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's, you know, get the camera, and, um, take a quick picture before we head out.Speaker 2: Okay, so, say cheese, everyone, and, oh, I hope you all have a great day at school.", "Image": "A kitchen table with a brown wood surface and silver metal legs holds a variety of items, including a wicker basket filled with whole fruits, a stainless steel lunch box, and a plastic container of carrot sticks. The table sits on a floor made of dark hardwood flooring in a straight plank pattern. A pair of black leather chairs with chrome frames are pushed against the table, beside a windowsill with a potted plant and a view of a frosty outdoor scene."}]</data>
      <data key="d18">["A kitchen table with a brown wood surface and silver metal legs holds a variety of items, including a wicker basket filled with whole fruits, a stainless steel lunch box, and a plastic container of carrot sticks. The table sits on a floor made of dark hardwood flooring in a straight plank pattern. A pair of black leather chairs with chrome frames are pushed against the table, beside a windowsill with a potted plant and a view of a frosty outdoor scene."]</data>
      <data key="d19">A kitchen table with a brown wood surface and silver metal legs holds a variety of items, including a wicker basket filled with whole fruits, a stainless steel lunch box, and a plastic container of carrot sticks. The table sits on a floor made of dark hardwood flooring in a straight plank pattern. A pair of black leather chairs with chrome frames are pushed against the table, beside a windowsill with a potted plant and a view of a frosty outdoor scene.</data>
