      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: Okay, so basically, I'm trying to get these lunches packed, um, you know, before you guys head out to school, right?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget to put the carrot sticks in, and, okay so, how about some hummus for dipping?Speaker 3: But why do I always have to have carrot sticks, actually, I know that they're good for me, but can I have a cookie instead?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a picture for my lunchbox, can you please put it in?Speaker 1: Uh, sure thing, kiddo, so, let me just, uh, finish making this sandwich, the thing is, we're running a bit behind schedule.Speaker 2: Remember when we used to make those bento boxes for school, how about we try that again sometime?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a picture in my lunchbox, why not me?Speaker 3: Because, actually, you didn't make one, so, maybe next time, you can draw something and we'll put it in your lunchbox.Speaker 1: So, uh, what's the plan for after school today, do we have any, um, activities or anything?Speaker 2: Okay, so, let me check the schedule, sweetie, it looks like you have soccer practice, and, oh, I need to pick up some more granola bars.Speaker 4: I want granola bars, mommy, please please</data>
