      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">oh, I need to pick up some more granola bars.Speaker 4: I want granola bars, mommy, please please can I have one now?Speaker 5: No, why, I don't want granola bars, I want goldfish crackers, look look, I have a goldfish cracker in my hand.Speaker 2: Sweetie, not now, okay, we'll have snacks after school, and, um, let's get your backpacks ready.Speaker 1: The thing is, I have a meeting at work, and, uh, I need to, you know, get going soon, so basically, let's hurry up.Speaker 3: But why do you have to go to work, actually, can't you just stay home with us?Speaker 2: Because, sweetie, daddy has to work to, you know, provide for our family, and, okay so, let's get moving.Speaker 4: Mommy, I don't want to go to school, I want to stay home and play with my toys, that's not fair.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I don't want to go to school, I want to play with blocks, look look, I'm building a castle.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's, you know, get our coats and, um, head out the door, the thing is, we don't want to be late.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's get going, sweetie, and, oh, don't forget your lunchboxes, and, um, have a great day at school.Speaker 3: Actually, I'm going to go get my backpack, can</data>
