      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">and, um, have a great day at school.Speaker 3: Actually, I'm going to go get my backpack, can I, uh, get a drink of water before we leave?Speaker 4: I want water, mommy, please please can I have a sip of water?Speaker 5: No, why, I don't want water, I want juice, look look, I have a juice box in my hand.Speaker 2: Sweetie, not now, okay, we'll have water at school, and, um, let's get going.Speaker 1: So, basically, let's, you know, get out the door, and, uh, have a great day, everyone, the thing is, I'll see you all after school.Speaker 3: But why do we have to leave so early, actually, I know that we don't want to be late, but can't we just, uh, leave a few minutes later?Speaker 2: Because, sweetie, we need to, you know, get to school on time, and, okay so, let's get moving.Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I'm wearing my favorite dress, can you please take a picture of me?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a picture, look look, I'm making a funny face.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's, you know, get the camera, and, um, take a quick picture before we head out.Speaker 2: Okay, so, say cheese, everyone, and, oh, I hope you all have a great day at school.</data>
