      <data key="d16">["Home, kitchen"]</data>
      <data key="d17">[{"Time": "2025-01-03 09:57:00", "Location": "Home, kitchen", "Audio": "Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking we should, you know, get the kids to school on time today, okay, because they have, like, a lot of work to do.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, that's a great idea, but first can you help me load the dishwasher, we have a lot of dishes from breakfast.Speaker 3: But why do I have to eat oatmeal, I don't like it, can I have cereal instead?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a picture of our family, can you hang it on the fridge?Speaker 1: Uh, yeah, sure thing, sweetie, I'll take a look, so, um, what's the picture of?Speaker 2: Okay, so, remember when we used to make pancakes on Fridays, how about we do that today?Speaker 3: Actually, I know how to make pancakes, can I help?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to help, why can't I?Speaker 1: The thing is, we don't have a lot of time, and, uh, we need to get the kids to school, so maybe next time, okay?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget to pack your lunch, you have a sandwich and some fruit, okay?Speaker 4: I want a sandwich cut into a fun shape, please, mommy, can you do that?Speaker 3: But why do I have to take a sandwich, I don't like sandwiches, can I have a salad instead?Speaker 1: Um, so, let me think about that, maybe we can, uh, make a salad for you, but you have to eat it in your lunchbox, okay?Speaker 2: Okay, so, how about we make a schedule for the day, and, you know, stick to it, so we can get everything done?Speaker 5: Look, look, I found a toy, it's a car, vroom, vroom.Speaker 4: Mommy, look, my picture is upside down, can you fix it?Speaker 1: So, uh, I'll take a look, and, um, I'll fix it for you, sweetie.Speaker 2: Okay, so, don't forget to take your vitamins, kids, we need to stay healthy, especially when it's cold outside.Speaker 3: I know that, mommy, I'm not a baby, I can take care of myself.Speaker 5: No, no, I don't want to take vitamins, why do I have to?Speaker 1: The thing is, vitamins are good for you, and, uh, they'll help you grow strong, so, um, just take them, okay?Speaker 2: Sweetie, can you please pass me the dish soap, I need to wash these dishes?Speaker 4: I want to wash the dishes, mommy, can I help?Speaker 3: But why do we have to wash the dishes, can't we just use paper plates?Speaker 1: Um, so, we can't use paper plates all the time, it's not good for the environment, and, uh, we need to be responsible.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's work together, kids, we can all help with the dishes, and, you know, make it fun.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to help, where's the soap?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I'm washing the dishes, see?Speaker 3: Actually, I'm doing a better job than you, I'm washing all the dishes.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's not fight, kids, we're all helping, and, um, that's what matters, okay?Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, you're doing a great job, just, you know, be careful not to break anything.Speaker 5: Look, look, I broke a dish, sorry, mommy.Speaker 4: That's not fair, he broke a dish, and now I'm in trouble.Speaker 1: Um, so, it's okay, accidents happen, and, uh, we'll just clean it up, okay?Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's finish loading the dishwasher, and, you know, get the kids to school on time.Speaker 3: But why do we have to hurry, can't we just take our time?Speaker 1: The thing is, we have a lot to do today, and, uh, we need to prioritize, so, um, let's just focus, okay?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget your backpack, you have a lot of homework to do tonight.Speaker 4: I want to do my homework now, mommy, can I?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to do homework, why can't I?Speaker 1: Um, so, not right now, kids, we need to, uh, get to school first, and, you know, then you can do your homework.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's get going, kids, we don't want to be late.Speaker 3: Actually, I'm ready, can we go now?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I'm ready, see?Speaker 1: So, uh, let's go, kids, we're all set, and, um, have a great day at school, okay?", "Image": "A view of a kitchen with dark gray laminate flooring and cream-colored cabinets. The countertops are made of white granite and are cluttered with morning breakfast dishes, including a bowl of oatmeal, a carton of orange juice, and a plate of toast. A stainless steel dishwasher stands open, partially loaded with dirty dishes, under a window with a view of a gloomy, overcast sky."}]</data>
      <data key="d18">["A view of a kitchen with dark gray laminate flooring and cream-colored cabinets. The countertops are made of white granite and are cluttered with morning breakfast dishes, including a bowl of oatmeal, a carton of orange juice, and a plate of toast. A stainless steel dishwasher stands open, partially loaded with dirty dishes, under a window with a view of a gloomy, overcast sky."]</data>
      <data key="d19">A view of a kitchen with dark gray laminate flooring and cream-colored cabinets. The countertops are made of white granite and are cluttered with morning breakfast dishes, including a bowl of oatmeal, a carton of orange juice, and a plate of toast. A stainless steel dishwasher stands open, partially loaded with dirty dishes, under a window with a view of a gloomy, overcast sky.</data>
