    <node id="SEGMENT_2025-01-03_EPISODE_002_CHUNK_0_0">
      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking we should, you know, get the kids to school on time today, okay, because they have, like, a lot of work to do.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, that's a great idea, but first can you help me load the dishwasher, we have a lot of dishes from breakfast.Speaker 3: But why do I have to eat oatmeal, I don't like it, can I have cereal instead?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a picture of our family, can you hang it on the fridge?Speaker 1: Uh, yeah, sure thing, sweetie, I'll take a look, so, um, what's the picture of?Speaker 2: Okay, so, remember when we used to make pancakes on Fridays, how about we do that today?Speaker 3: Actually, I know how to make pancakes, can I help?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to help, why can't I?Speaker 1: The thing is, we don't have a lot of time, and, uh, we need to get the kids to school, so maybe next time, okay?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget to pack your lunch, you have a sandwich and some fruit, okay?Speaker 4: I want a sandwich cut into a fun shape, please, mommy, can you do that?Speaker 3: But why do I have to take a sandwich, I don't like sandwiches, can I have a salad instead?Speaker 1: Um, so, let me think about that,</data>
      <data key="d21">1199</data>
