      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">use paper plates?Speaker 1: Um, so, we can't use paper plates all the time, it's not good for the environment, and, uh, we need to be responsible.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's work together, kids, we can all help with the dishes, and, you know, make it fun.Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to help, where's the soap?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I'm washing the dishes, see?Speaker 3: Actually, I'm doing a better job than you, I'm washing all the dishes.Speaker 1: So, uh, let's not fight, kids, we're all helping, and, um, that's what matters, okay?Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, you're doing a great job, just, you know, be careful not to break anything.Speaker 5: Look, look, I broke a dish, sorry, mommy.Speaker 4: That's not fair, he broke a dish, and now I'm in trouble.Speaker 1: Um, so, it's okay, accidents happen, and, uh, we'll just clean it up, okay?Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's finish loading the dishwasher, and, you know, get the kids to school on time.Speaker 3: But why do we have to hurry, can't we just take our time?Speaker 1: The thing is, we have a lot to do today, and, uh, we need to prioritize, so, um, let's just focus, okay?Speaker 2: Sweetie, don't forget your backpack, you have a lot</data>
