      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: So basically, I was thinking, um, we should probably get the kids' school stuff organized for next semester, you know?Speaker 2: Okay so, I was looking at the calendar and I think we have a parent-teacher conference coming up, sweetie, remember when we had to do that last year?Speaker 1: The thing is, I'm not sure if I can make it, I have a meeting at work that I really need to be at, um, it's about this new project we're starting.Speaker 2: How about I go to the conference and you can, you know, catch up with the teacher later, maybe over email or something?Speaker 3: Mommy, Mommy, can I have a snack?Speaker 2: Sweetie, not right now, we're in a meeting, okay?Speaker 1: So, uh, what were we talking about again?Speaker 2: The parent-teacher conference, and I was saying maybe I can go and you can follow up with the teacher later.Speaker 3: But I'm hungry, Mommy, I want goldfish crackers!Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, just a minute, Mommy's busy right now.Speaker 1: You know, I was thinking, um, maybe we can, like, prep some meals for the week, you know, to make mornings easier?Speaker 2: That's a great idea, sweetie, how about we make some, uh, pasta salad or something?Speaker</data>
