    <node id="SEGMENT_2025-01-03_EPISODE_004">
      <data key="d0">EPISODE</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d7">[12:46:00] Local noodle shop, Huangpu District: Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we sh...</data>
      <data key="d8">101</data>
      <data key="d9">4</data>
      <data key="d10">2025-01-03</data>
      <data key="d2">2025-01-03</data>
      <data key="d11">4</data>
      <data key="d12">4</data>
      <data key="d3">[12:46:00] Local noo...</data>
      <data key="d13">EPISODE</data>
      <data key="d14">2025-01-03 12:46:00</data>
      <data key="d15">2025-01-03 12:46:00</data>
      <data key="d16">["Local noodle shop, Huangpu District"]</data>
      <data key="d17">[{"Time": "2025-01-03 12:46:00", "Location": "Local noodle shop, Huangpu District", "Audio": "Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we should probably get the kids to eat more vegetables, right, because, I mean, they're not getting enough, you know, nutrients and stuff.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, that's a great idea, but, you know, they're really picky, so, like, we need to find ways to make it more, uh, appealing to them, I guess.Speaker 3: (child) Mommy, Mommy, can I have more noodles?Speaker 2: Not right now, sweetie, you need to finish your vegetables first, remember when we talked about eating healthy?Speaker 1: Yeah, and, uh, so basically, the thing is, we should, you know, set a good example, so, like, we need to eat more veggies too, right?Speaker 4: (child) Daddy, look at this! I made a tower with my chopsticks!Speaker 2: That's great, sweetie, but, okay, so, let's focus on eating, and then you can play, how about that?Speaker 1: So, um, I was talking to, uh, John at work, and, you know, he was saying that, like, his kids are really into, uh, sports, and, so, like, we should probably get our kids into something like that too.Speaker 3: (child) I want to play with blocks! Can we get blocks, Mommy?Speaker 2: We'll see, sweetie, okay, so, let's finish lunch first, and then we can talk about it, sound good?Speaker 4: (child) I don't like this soup! It's too salty!Speaker 1: Okay, okay, so, like, we can get you something else, but, you know, you need to try new things, and, uh, it's good for you, I think.Speaker 2: Sweetie, remember when we went to the park, and you tried, uh, new swings, and you liked it, right?Speaker 3: (child) Yeah! And I went \"Wheeee!\" all the way down!Speaker 1:  Yeah, that was, uh, really funny, and, so, like, we should take them to the park again soon, maybe this weekend?Speaker 2: That sounds like a great idea, okay, so, let's, uh, check the weather forecast, and, you know, make sure it's not, like, too cold or anything.Speaker 4: (child) I'm cold! Can I have a blanket, Mommy?Speaker 2: Sweetie, we're inside, it's warm, you don't need a blanket, but, okay, so, let's, uh, get you a jacket or something if you're still cold.Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we should probably, uh, start looking into, like, summer camps or something for the kids, because, you know, it's, like, already January, and, so, like, time flies, right?Speaker 3: (child) I want to go to camp! Can I bring my toys?Speaker 2: We'll see, sweetie, okay, so, let's, uh, talk about it later, and, you know, figure out what's best for everyone, sound good?Speaker 4: (child) Mommy, can I have a cookie?Speaker 1:  Not right now, buddy, you just had lunch, and, uh, too many cookies are, like, not good for you, I think.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, how about we, uh, get you a fruit or something instead, and, you know, that way you'll be healthy and happy, right?Speaker 3: (child) I want a banana! No, wait, I want an apple!Speaker 1:  Okay, okay, so, like, we can get you an apple, and, uh, that's a great choice, I think.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's, uh, finish up here, and, you know, get the kids back to school on time, sound good?Speaker 4: (child) I don't want to go to school! I want to play!Speaker 1:  I know, buddy, but, you know, school is, like, important, and, uh, you need to learn and grow, right?Speaker 2: Sweetie, remember when you learned, uh, new things in school, and you were so proud of yourself, right?Speaker 3: (child) Yeah! I learned about, uh, dinosaurs!Speaker 1:  That's great, buddy, and, uh, so, like, we're proud of you too, and, you know, we'll, uh, get through this together, as a family, right?", "Image": "A steaming bowl of noodles sits on a worn, dark wood table with a pair of chopsticks and a small bowl of sliced green onions. The table stands on a floor made of gray terrazzo tiles, surrounded by simple, modern chairs with black metal frames and red plastic seats. A row of large, silver metal steamers lines the counter behind the table, under a bank of fluorescent lights with a warm, yellowish glow."}]</data>
      <data key="d18">["A steaming bowl of noodles sits on a worn, dark wood table with a pair of chopsticks and a small bowl of sliced green onions. The table stands on a floor made of gray terrazzo tiles, surrounded by simple, modern chairs with black metal frames and red plastic seats. A row of large, silver metal steamers lines the counter behind the table, under a bank of fluorescent lights with a warm, yellowish glow."]</data>
      <data key="d19">A steaming bowl of noodles sits on a worn, dark wood table with a pair of chopsticks and a small bowl of sliced green onions. The table stands on a floor made of gray terrazzo tiles, surrounded by simple, modern chairs with black metal frames and red plastic seats. A row of large, silver metal steamers lines the counter behind the table, under a bank of fluorescent lights with a warm, yellowish glow.</data>
