      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we should probably get the kids to eat more vegetables, right, because, I mean, they're not getting enough, you know, nutrients and stuff.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, that's a great idea, but, you know, they're really picky, so, like, we need to find ways to make it more, uh, appealing to them, I guess.Speaker 3: (child) Mommy, Mommy, can I have more noodles?Speaker 2: Not right now, sweetie, you need to finish your vegetables first, remember when we talked about eating healthy?Speaker 1: Yeah, and, uh, so basically, the thing is, we should, you know, set a good example, so, like, we need to eat more veggies too, right?Speaker 4: (child) Daddy, look at this! I made a tower with my chopsticks!Speaker 2: That's great, sweetie, but, okay, so, let's focus on eating, and then you can play, how about that?Speaker 1: So, um, I was talking to, uh, John at work, and, you know, he was saying that, like, his kids are really into, uh, sports, and, so, like, we should probably get our kids into something like that too.Speaker 3: (child) I want to play with blocks! Can we get blocks, Mommy?Speaker 2: We'll see, sweetie, okay, so, let's finish lunch</data>
