    <node id="SEGMENT_2025-01-03_EPISODE_004_CHUNK_0_2">
      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">summer camps or something for the kids, because, you know, it's, like, already January, and, so, like, time flies, right?Speaker 3: (child) I want to go to camp! Can I bring my toys?Speaker 2: We'll see, sweetie, okay, so, let's, uh, talk about it later, and, you know, figure out what's best for everyone, sound good?Speaker 4: (child) Mommy, can I have a cookie?Speaker 1:  Not right now, buddy, you just had lunch, and, uh, too many cookies are, like, not good for you, I think.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, how about we, uh, get you a fruit or something instead, and, you know, that way you'll be healthy and happy, right?Speaker 3: (child) I want a banana! No, wait, I want an apple!Speaker 1:  Okay, okay, so, like, we can get you an apple, and, uh, that's a great choice, I think.Speaker 2: Okay, so, let's, uh, finish up here, and, you know, get the kids back to school on time, sound good?Speaker 4: (child) I don't want to go to school! I want to play!Speaker 1:  I know, buddy, but, you know, school is, like, important, and, uh, you need to learn and grow, right?Speaker 2: Sweetie, remember when you learned, uh, new things in school, and you were so proud of yourself, right?Speaker 3:</data>
      <data key="d21">1195</data>
      <data key="d22">[]</data>
      <data key="d23">{}</data>
      <data key="d3">summer camps or some...</data>
