      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: So I was thinking, you know, we should probably get the kids to eat something before we head out, um, to their piano lessons, the thing is, they've been starving all morningSpeaker 2: Daddy, I wanna get a cookie, can I get a cookie?Speaker 1: Uh, well, let's see, so basically, we need to get you guys to eat something healthy first, like, you know, a sandwich or somethingSpeaker 3: But why, I don't wanna eat a sandwich, I hate sandwichesSpeaker 2: Yeah, I hate sandwiches too, can we get pizza?Speaker 1: Um, no, not pizza, so, the thing is, we just had pizza for dinner last night, you know?Speaker 4: Look, Daddy, a bird outside, can we feed it?Speaker 1: Uh, no, not right now, so, we need to focus on getting you guys to eat something, like, you know, some fruit or somethingSpeaker 2: I wanna eat a cookie, pleeease?Speaker 3: Yeah, me too, I wanna eat a cookieSpeaker 1: Okay, fine, so, one cookie each, but just one, you know?Speaker 4: Yay, thank you, Daddy, can we get hot chocolate too?Speaker 1: Um, well, let's see, so basically, we need to get going soon, but, uh, yeah, sure, you can get hot chocolateSpeaker 2: I wanna put whipped cream on my hot chocolate, can I?Speaker</data>
