      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">Speaker 2: Okay so I'm trying to organize these documents, um, for the Johnson project, sweetie, can you please not touch those papers?Speaker 2: So, I was thinking, how about we, uh, make a folder for each client, and then, like, subfolders for their projects?Speaker 2: Remember when we did that for the Smith account, it was, like, really helpful, right?Speaker 2: Okay, so, let me just, uh, find this one document, it's, like, really important, and, oh, here it is, sweetie, can you please hand me that stapler?Speaker 2: Um, so, I was thinking, maybe we can, like, have a meeting with the team, to, you know, discuss the project, and, uh, make sure everyone's on the same page?Speaker 2: How about, like, next Wednesday, at, um, 2 o'clock, does that work for you, sweetie?Speaker 2: Okay, so, I'll, uh, send out an email, and, like, make sure everyone knows, and, oh, can you please pass me that pen?Speaker 2: So, I was thinking, maybe we can, like, order some lunch, for the meeting, and, uh, get some sandwiches, or, like, pizza?Speaker 2: Um, what do you think, sweetie, should we, like, get something healthy, or, like, just get, uh, whatever everyone wants?Speaker 2: Okay, so, I'll, like,</data>
