      <data key="d16">["Subway Line 2, Shanghai"]</data>
      <data key="d17">[{"Time": "2025-01-03 18:14:00", "Location": "Subway Line 2, Shanghai", "Audio": "Speaker 1: So basically, I had a meeting at work today, and, uh, it was pretty long, you know, we were discussing this new project, and, um, I think it's gonna be a big deal, but, so, I'm not really sure how it's gonna affect my schedule, yet.Speaker 2: Okay, so, how was your day, sweetie, I mean, aside from the meeting, did you, uh, get a chance to, you know, grab some lunch?Speaker 3: Daddy, Daddy, I'm hungry, can we get some dumplings when we get home?Speaker 1: Um, yeah, sure thing, kiddo, we'll, uh, see what Mom says, okay?Speaker 2: How about we make some noodles instead, sweetie, we have some vegetables at home that need to be used up, remember when we went to the market last weekend?Speaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, look at this! I drew a picture of our cat, Mr. Whiskers!Speaker 2: Oh, that's so cute, sweetie, let me see, um, what's Mr. Whiskers doing in the picture?Speaker 1: So, anyway, like I was saying, this project at work, it's, uh, gonna be a challenge, but, you know, I think we can handle it, the thing is, we need to, um, work together as a team.Speaker 3: Daddy, can I play with my toy car when we get home, pleeease?Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, but first, let's get some dinner, and then you can play, how about we make it a quick dinner, so we can, you know, get some rest?Speaker 1: Um, yeah, that sounds like a plan, so, uh, what time do the kids have school tomorrow, again?Speaker 2: Let me check the schedule, okay, so, it looks like they have, um, a half-day tomorrow, and then they're off on Monday, for the holiday.Speaker 4: Mommy, I don't wanna go to school tomorrow, I wanna stay home and play!Speaker 1: Ah, come on, kiddo, you gotta go to school, it's, uh, important, you know, for your education, and, um, you'll see your friends, right?Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's not, uh, argue about this now, we can, you know, talk about it when we get home, how about we listen to some music, instead?Speaker 3: Yeah! Can we listen to the Frozen soundtrack, pleeease?Speaker 1: Um, sure thing, kiddo, we'll, uh, put it on when we get home, so, uh, let's just, you know, relax for now, and, um, enjoy the ride.Speaker 2: Okay, so, I was thinking, maybe we can, uh, go to the park on Monday, since the kids are off, and, you know, it's a holiday, how about we pack a picnic lunch?Speaker 4: Yay! Can I bring my ball, Mommy?Speaker 1: Um, yeah, sure thing, kiddo, we'll, uh, bring the ball, and, you know, have a nice time, the thing is, we need to, um, check the weather, first.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's check the forecast when we get home, and, um, see if it's, you know, gonna be a nice day, outside.Speaker 3: Daddy, I'm still hungry, can we get some snacks, pleeease?Speaker 1: Um, okay, kiddo, we'll, uh, get some snacks, when we get off the subway, okay?Speaker 2: How about we get some, uh, fruit, or, you know, some granola bars, something healthy, sweetie?Speaker 4: Mommy, can I have a cookie, instead?Speaker 1: Um, well, let's, uh, see, kiddo, we'll, you know, think about it, the thing is, we don't want, uh, too much sugar, before dinner.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's, uh, compromise, we can, you know, get a cookie, but, um, just one, and, you know, make sure to, uh, brush your teeth, afterwards.Speaker 3: Yay! Thank you, Mommy!Speaker 1: So, anyway, like I was saying, this project at work, it's, uh, gonna be a challenge, but, you know, I think we can handle it, the thing is, we need to, um, work together, as a team.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's, uh, focus on getting home, first, and, um, then we can, you know, talk about work, and, uh, everything else, okay?Speaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, I see our stop, can we get off, now?Speaker 1: Um, yeah, kiddo, we're, uh, getting off, now, let's, you know, gather our stuff, and, um, head home.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's, uh, get moving, we're, you know, almost home, and, um, we can, you know, relax, soon.", "Image": "A crowded subway train with grey plastic seats and silver poles, illuminated by fluorescent lights overhead. The floor is made of dark grey linoleum with yellow warning strips near the doors. A forest of black umbrellas and dark winter coats fills the frame, with glimpses of advertisements on the train's walls, featuring bright colors and Chinese characters."}]</data>
      <data key="d18">["A crowded subway train with grey plastic seats and silver poles, illuminated by fluorescent lights overhead. The floor is made of dark grey linoleum with yellow warning strips near the doors. A forest of black umbrellas and dark winter coats fills the frame, with glimpses of advertisements on the train's walls, featuring bright colors and Chinese characters."]</data>
      <data key="d19">A crowded subway train with grey plastic seats and silver poles, illuminated by fluorescent lights overhead. The floor is made of dark grey linoleum with yellow warning strips near the doors. A forest of black umbrellas and dark winter coats fills the frame, with glimpses of advertisements on the train's walls, featuring bright colors and Chinese characters.</data>
