      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">park on Monday, since the kids are off, and, you know, it's a holiday, how about we pack a picnic lunch?Speaker 4: Yay! Can I bring my ball, Mommy?Speaker 1: Um, yeah, sure thing, kiddo, we'll, uh, bring the ball, and, you know, have a nice time, the thing is, we need to, um, check the weather, first.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's check the forecast when we get home, and, um, see if it's, you know, gonna be a nice day, outside.Speaker 3: Daddy, I'm still hungry, can we get some snacks, pleeease?Speaker 1: Um, okay, kiddo, we'll, uh, get some snacks, when we get off the subway, okay?Speaker 2: How about we get some, uh, fruit, or, you know, some granola bars, something healthy, sweetie?Speaker 4: Mommy, can I have a cookie, instead?Speaker 1: Um, well, let's, uh, see, kiddo, we'll, you know, think about it, the thing is, we don't want, uh, too much sugar, before dinner.Speaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's, uh, compromise, we can, you know, get a cookie, but, um, just one, and, you know, make sure to, uh, brush your teeth, afterwards.Speaker 3: Yay! Thank you, Mommy!Speaker 1: So, anyway, like I was saying, this project at work, it's, uh, gonna be a challenge, but, you know, I think we</data>
