      <data key="d17">[{"Time": "2025-01-03 19:07:00", "Location": "Local noodle shop, Huangpu District", "Audio": "Speaker 1: So, um, how was everyone's day, you know, anything exciting happen?Speaker 2: Okay, so, the kids had a pretty good day, I think, sweetie, didn't you have a test at school today?Speaker 3: Actually, I got a 90 on my math test, and, but why do I have to take so many tests, anyway?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a picture in art class, can I show you?Speaker 1: That's great, sweetie, um, let me take a look, so basically, what's, uh, what's the picture of?Speaker 2: Okay, honey, let Daddy look at it after we order, how about we get some noodles, who wants what?Speaker 3: I want the beef ones, but why can't we get the spicy ones, they're more fun?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want beef, no, I want chicken, why can't I have chicken?Speaker 4: That's not fair, I wanted chicken, please please can I have chicken too?Speaker 1: So, um, let's see, we can get a few different kinds, you know, to share, the thing is, we need to make sure everyone gets something they likeSpeaker 2: Okay, so, how about we get two beef and one chicken, and, sweetie, you can have a little bit of both?Speaker 3: But why do we have to share, I don't want to share my noodles?Speaker 5: Look, look, a snowflake, why is it snowing, Daddy?Speaker 1: So, uh, it's snowing because it's cold outside, and, you know, the weather is, um, pretty bad todaySpeaker 2: Okay, honey, let's not get too distracted, remember when we went to the park last week, and it was so much fun?Speaker 4: Mommy, I want to go to the park again, can we go tomorrow, please?Speaker 3: Actually, I don't think it's a good idea, because, but why would we go to the park when it's freezing outside?Speaker 1: So, um, we'll see, you know, maybe we can find something else to do, like, uh, going to the museum or somethingSpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, how about we plan something for next weekend?Speaker 5: No, no, I want to go to the park, why can't we go to the park, Daddy?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a snowman on my plate, can I have a cookie now?Speaker 1: So, uh, let's finish our dinner first, and, you know, then we can think about dessert, the thing is, we need to make sure we eat our vegetables tooSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, just a few more bites, and, remember, we need to get you kids to bed on time, because school tomorrowSpeaker 3: But why do we have to go to bed so early, it's not fair, all my friends get to stay up laterSpeaker 5: Me too, me too, I don't want to go to bed, why do I have to go to bed?Speaker 1: So, um, because you need to get some rest, and, you know, be ready for school tomorrow, that's just the way it isSpeaker 2: Okay, honey, let's not argue, how about we make a deal, if you finish your dinner, we can read a book together before bed?Speaker 4: Yeah, yeah, I want to read a book, Mommy, can I pick the book?Speaker 3: Actually, I want to pick the book, because, but why does she get to pick, it's not fair?Speaker 1: So, uh, we'll see, you know, maybe we can take turns picking the book, the thing is, we need to make sure everyone is happySpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, sweetie, you can pick the book tonight, and, honey, you can pick it tomorrow nightSpeaker 5: Look, look, I spilled my juice, why did I spill my juice, Daddy?Speaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, he spilled his juice, that's not fair, I didn't spill my juiceSpeaker 1: So, um, it's okay, accidents happen, and, you know, we can just clean it up, no big dealSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's just calm down, and, remember, we're all together, and that's what mattersSpeaker 3: Actually, can I have a napkin, because, but why do I have to use a dirty napkin, can't I have a clean one?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a napkin, why can't I have a napkin?Speaker 1: So, uh, here you go, you know, now let's just finish our dinner, and, the thing is, we need to get going soonSpeaker 2: Okay, honey, just a few more minutes, and, sweetie, don't forget to drink your waterSpeaker 4: Mommy, I'm done, can I have a cookie now, please please?Speaker 3: But why does she get a cookie, it's not fair, I want a cookie tooSpeaker 1: So, um, we'll see, you know, maybe we can get some cookies on the way home, the thing is, we need to make sure we don't eat too much sugarSpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, sweetie, we can get some cookies, and, honey, you can have a special treat tooSpeaker 5: Yay, yay, I want a cookie, thank you, DaddySpeaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, can we go now, I'm tired, please?Speaker 1: So, uh, yeah, let's get going, you know, it's getting late, and, the thing is, we need to get you kids to bedSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's go, and, remember, we'll have a fun weekend, I promiseSpeaker 3: Actually, can I ask you something, Daddy, but why do we have to go to school on Monday?Speaker 1: So, um, because you need to learn, and, you know, education is important, the thing is, it's just the way it isSpeaker 2: Okay, honey, let's talk about it later, and, sweetie, let's just get going, okay?", "Image": "A steaming hot noodle dish sits on a round, wooden table with a red tablecloth, surrounded by five wooden chairs with curved backs. The table holds a variety of dishes, including a plate of dumplings, a bowl of wonton soup, and a teapot with steam rising from its spout. The flooring is made of dark gray tile, and the walls are painted a warm, golden yellow, with soft light emanating from overhead lanterns."}]</data>
      <data key="d18">["A steaming hot noodle dish sits on a round, wooden table with a red tablecloth, surrounded by five wooden chairs with curved backs. The table holds a variety of dishes, including a plate of dumplings, a bowl of wonton soup, and a teapot with steam rising from its spout. The flooring is made of dark gray tile, and the walls are painted a warm, golden yellow, with soft light emanating from overhead lanterns."]</data>
      <data key="d19">A steaming hot noodle dish sits on a round, wooden table with a red tablecloth, surrounded by five wooden chairs with curved backs. The table holds a variety of dishes, including a plate of dumplings, a bowl of wonton soup, and a teapot with steam rising from its spout. The flooring is made of dark gray tile, and the walls are painted a warm, golden yellow, with soft light emanating from overhead lanterns.</data>
