      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">But why do we have to share, I don't want to share my noodles?Speaker 5: Look, look, a snowflake, why is it snowing, Daddy?Speaker 1: So, uh, it's snowing because it's cold outside, and, you know, the weather is, um, pretty bad todaySpeaker 2: Okay, honey, let's not get too distracted, remember when we went to the park last week, and it was so much fun?Speaker 4: Mommy, I want to go to the park again, can we go tomorrow, please?Speaker 3: Actually, I don't think it's a good idea, because, but why would we go to the park when it's freezing outside?Speaker 1: So, um, we'll see, you know, maybe we can find something else to do, like, uh, going to the museum or somethingSpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, how about we plan something for next weekend?Speaker 5: No, no, I want to go to the park, why can't we go to the park, Daddy?Speaker 4: Mommy, look, I made a snowman on my plate, can I have a cookie now?Speaker 1: So, uh, let's finish our dinner first, and, you know, then we can think about dessert, the thing is, we need to make sure we eat our vegetables tooSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, just a few more bites, and, remember, we need to get you kids to bed on time, because</data>
