    <node id="SEGMENT_2025-01-03_EPISODE_008_CHUNK_0_2">
      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">sweetie, just a few more bites, and, remember, we need to get you kids to bed on time, because school tomorrowSpeaker 3: But why do we have to go to bed so early, it's not fair, all my friends get to stay up laterSpeaker 5: Me too, me too, I don't want to go to bed, why do I have to go to bed?Speaker 1: So, um, because you need to get some rest, and, you know, be ready for school tomorrow, that's just the way it isSpeaker 2: Okay, honey, let's not argue, how about we make a deal, if you finish your dinner, we can read a book together before bed?Speaker 4: Yeah, yeah, I want to read a book, Mommy, can I pick the book?Speaker 3: Actually, I want to pick the book, because, but why does she get to pick, it's not fair?Speaker 1: So, uh, we'll see, you know, maybe we can take turns picking the book, the thing is, we need to make sure everyone is happySpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, sweetie, you can pick the book tonight, and, honey, you can pick it tomorrow nightSpeaker 5: Look, look, I spilled my juice, why did I spill my juice, Daddy?Speaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, he spilled his juice, that's not fair, I didn't spill my juiceSpeaker 1: So, um, it's okay, accidents</data>
