      <data key="d0">CHUNK</data>
      <data key="d1">lexical_graph</data>
      <data key="d20">spilled his juice, that's not fair, I didn't spill my juiceSpeaker 1: So, um, it's okay, accidents happen, and, you know, we can just clean it up, no big dealSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, let's just calm down, and, remember, we're all together, and that's what mattersSpeaker 3: Actually, can I have a napkin, because, but why do I have to use a dirty napkin, can't I have a clean one?Speaker 5: Me too, me too, I want a napkin, why can't I have a napkin?Speaker 1: So, uh, here you go, you know, now let's just finish our dinner, and, the thing is, we need to get going soonSpeaker 2: Okay, honey, just a few more minutes, and, sweetie, don't forget to drink your waterSpeaker 4: Mommy, I'm done, can I have a cookie now, please please?Speaker 3: But why does she get a cookie, it's not fair, I want a cookie tooSpeaker 1: So, um, we'll see, you know, maybe we can get some cookies on the way home, the thing is, we need to make sure we don't eat too much sugarSpeaker 2: Okay, so, that sounds like a great idea, sweetie, we can get some cookies, and, honey, you can have a special treat tooSpeaker 5: Yay, yay, I want a cookie, thank you, DaddySpeaker 4: Mommy, Mommy, can we go now, I'm tired,</data>
