      <data key="d20">Speaker 1: Okay, so, um, let's get the kids ready for bed, you know, it's already pretty lateSpeaker 2: Sweetie, I think we should, okay so, have them brush their teeth first, and then we can read a bookSpeaker 3: But why do I have to go to bed so early, I'm not tired, actually, I was just reading this really cool bookSpeaker 4: Mommy look, I made a picture, can I show it to you, please pleaseSpeaker 1: Uh, yeah, sure thing, sweetie, let me just, you know, finish talking to mom for a secondSpeaker 2: Remember when we used to have to wake them up early for school, now they just want to stay up all nightSpeaker 5: Me too, me too, I want to stay up, why do I have to go to bedSpeaker 3: Because you're little, and you need to sleep, so your body can grow strongSpeaker 4: That's not fair, I'm big too, I can stay up, look look, I can touch the ceilingSpeaker 1: So, uh, what's for breakfast tomorrow, did we decide on, um, pancakes or wafflesSpeaker 2: Oh, I think we said pancakes, but we need to get some more syrup, I don't think we have enoughSpeaker 5: I want syrup, I love syrup, can I have some nowSpeaker 3: No, you can't have syrup now, it's too close to bedtime, and it's not good for</data>
