      <data key="d20">some nowSpeaker 3: No, you can't have syrup now, it's too close to bedtime, and it's not good for youSpeaker 4: Mommy, can I have a glass of water, I'm thirstySpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, I'll get you a glass of water, but then you need to get ready for bedSpeaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we should, uh, start getting them to pack their own lunches, it's time they learnedSpeaker 3: But why do I have to pack my own lunch, can't you just do it for meSpeaker 5: I want to pack my lunch, I can do it, look look, I can make a sandwichSpeaker 2: That's a great idea, sweetie, you can help us pack your lunch, and learn how to make a sandwichSpeaker 4: Mommy look, my toothbrush is pink, and my brother's is blueSpeaker 1: Uh, yeah, that's right, sweetie, you have a pink toothbrush, and your brother has a blue oneSpeaker 3: Actually, I know that, can I go brush my teeth nowSpeaker 2: Okay, sweetie, go brush your teeth, and then we'll read a bookSpeaker 5: I want to brush my teeth too, me tooSpeaker 1: So, um, I was thinking, you know, we should, uh, start a, uh, schedule for the kids, so they know what to expectSpeaker 2: That's a great idea, sweetie, we can make a schedule, and post</data>
